Freshly procured porcine cornea was mounted on a previously described diffusion cell [35, 37]. The receptor compartment comprised freshly prepared glutathione bicarbonate ringer (GBR) containing 2% ethanol as the diffusion medium (20 ± 2 ml), stirred continuously (50 rpm) at 37 ± 0.2 °C. Ethanol was added in the diffusion medium to maintain sink conditions [38]. ATS-SLNs (0.2 ml) placed on the porcine cornea represent the donor side. Samples were withdrawn at various time points with replacement and were analyzed spectrophotometrically at 246 nm after suitable dilution. The apparent corneal permeability coefficient (Papp) and steady-state flux of both ATS-SLNs and ATS-SUS were determined, as reported previously [35, 37]. At the end of the experiment, each cornea (free from any adjoining tissue, viz. sclera) was weighed (Ww). Then, it was soaked in 1 ml methanol, dried overnight at 90 °C, and reweighed (Wr). The corneal hydration level (HL%) was calculated by the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
